Day 3: Entity-Relationship (ER) Model

Topic:
Entity-Relationship (ER) Model

Learning Objectives:

Understand entities, attributes, and relationships
Learn about cardinality (one-to-one, one-to-many, many-to-many)
Understand weak entities and their role
Learn ER diagram notation and how to represent data visually

Activities / Deliverables:

Design an ER diagram for a Library Management System from scratch
Identify entities (Books, Members, Librarian, etc.)
Define attributes and relationships between entities
Apply proper ER notation and cardinality
Create a clean and well-structured diagram

Tools / Tech:

Draw.io (for ER diagram creation)
MySQL Workbench (for visual modeling and practice)

